cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about generating text, which falls under the natural language processing (NLP) domain. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model and learning algorithm for generative adversarial networks (GANs), which is related to machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI), making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also mentions the use of Gumbel-Softmax relaxation, which is a technique commonly used in neural networks for discrete data, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper mentions the use of hierarchical evolutionary learning, which is a technique used in optimization and search algorithms, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a less likely but still possible sub-category.
